Package org.midica.file

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    IParser
    This interface can be implemented by parser classes which can parse an input file.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    CharsetUtils
    This class provides charset-dependent methods.
    CommandOption
    Objects of this class represent a MidicaPL command option.
    ConfirmDialog
    This class provides a confirm dialog implementing the same look and feel as the other components.
    Exporter
    This class can be extended by exporter classes which write a music file based on a MIDI sequence.
    ExportResult
    This class is used to collect export warnings for a later display.
    Instrument
    Objects of this class represent a specific MIDI channel.
    MidicaPLExporter
    This class is used to export the currently loaded MIDI sequence as a MidicaPL source file.
    MidicaPLParser
    This class is used to parse a MidicaPL source file.
    MidiExporter
    This class is used to export the currently loaded MIDI sequence as a MIDI file.
    MidiParser
    An object of this class can be used in order to parse a MIDI file.
    NamedInteger
    This class is used to provide integers, associated with a name string.
    NestableBlock
    This class represents a nestable block, used by the MidicaPL parser.
    SequenceParser
    This class can be extended by specialized parser classes which parse an input file and create a MIDI sequence.
    SoundfontParser
    This class is used in order to load a user-defined soundfont file.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    ExportException
    This class is used for exceptions that can occur during a file export process.
    ParseException
    Exceptions of this class can be thrown if an error occurs while parsing a file.
